      "writtenOn": "2019-10-09T17:57:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, though as far as I can tell, probably only if you really care about memory usage. The libx264 encoding is fast and already itself threaded.\n\nIt\u0027d also be trivially easy to just break into several smaller batches instead of having to bother with really streaming, e.g. instead of\n\n   rasterize(0..n)\n   addFrames(0..n)\n\nwe could\n\n   rasterize(0..k)\n   addFrames(0..k)\n   rasterize(k..2k)\n   addFrames(k..2k)\n   ...\n   rasterize(n-k..n)\n   addFrames(n-k..n)",
